          "opening": {
            "uid": "1962475876330803682",
            "title": "n8n workflow and AI agents specialist needed for eCommerce Plateform",
            "description": "We’re an eCommerce brand looking for someone to help us automate a few key parts of our business using n8n and smart, lightweight AI tools (think GPT-powered tasks, not full-on AI systems).\n\nThis is a short-term gig — probably a couple weeks of focused work — but we’re open to ongoing support if it’s a good fit.\n\nWhat You’ll Work On:\n\nBuild useful, clean n8n workflows to connect tools we already use (Shopify, Notion, Slack, Google Sheets, etc.)\n\nUse agentic AI in practical ways — like auto-tagging products, summarizing customer feedback, or drafting internal updates\n\nKeep the flows clear, reusable, and easy for non-technical teammates to understand\n\nSuggest improvements — we’re open to ideas, not just execution\n\nYou’re a Good Fit If:\n\nYou’ve built with n8n, Zapier, Make, or similar tools\n\nYou know how to use AI tools in real-world, low-hype ways\n\nYou work independently, communicate clearly, and enjoy building stuff that works\n\nYou’re chill, detail-oriented, and not into overcomplicating things\n\nBonus (not required):\n\nExperience in eCommerce or DTC\n\nLight scripting skills (JavaScript or Python)\n\nSome AI prompt engineering know-how\n\nWe care about working with people who are thoughtful, collaborative, and easy to work with — from any background. If this sounds like your kind of project, shoot us a quick message with a few examples of your work.\n\nLet’s keep it simple and make something useful.",
